    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="581"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.458/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Shah of Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reza Shah Pahlavi</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-17">March 17,
                            1938</date>.<lb/>[Received March 17—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I sincerely thank Your Excellency for the kind good wishes and felicitations
                    which you have been so good as to formulate on the occasion of my anniversary
                    and the New Year and I express reciprocal wishes and my desires for the
                    consolidation of the bonds of friendship between our two nations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reza Shah Pahlavi</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
